  <channel>
    <title>Refugees contributor: Richard Hall</title>
    <description>Richard Hall is a correspondent for Public Radio International’s The World and PRI.org, covering the Middle East from his home base in Lebanon. He has reported across the region since 2009, covering Lebanon, Iraq, Syria and Turkey. Richard has written extensively on the Syrian civil war and the rise of the Islamic State. His reporting on the Kurdish issue has taken him across Turkey and up the Qandil Mountains in northern Iraq.
</description>
